    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, slice your <strong>cucumber </strong>into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Combine your<strong> sambal oelek</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s] </strong>(not sure about citrus? Try using less!)<strong> </strong>in the reserved bowl with the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>sambal dipping sauce</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime[s]</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
